    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"shock troops\" is an interesting way to put it lol. i guess since they're the first to go in and fight, do they ever get overwhelmed or depleted if the infection is too intense? like is there a specific way the body signals that it needs more of them sent in immediately?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the body can absolutely get overwhelmed, leading to neutropenia if the production or release is insufficient for the demand. The immediate signaling mechanism is primarily through chemical mediators like chemokines and cytokines, such as G-CSF. These signals act on the bone marrow to dramatically increase the production and release of neutrophils into the bloodstream to meet the overwhelming demand. If the infection is too severe, the demand outstrips the supply, which is a critical concept for board questions.",
